<h3 id="header">Drab Tests</h3>
<p>
  This application is for debugging and testing Drab.
</p>

If you started it with <code>iex -S mix phoenix.server</code>, you may debug Drab functions in IEx by following the instruction in the console:
<pre>
[debug] 
    Started Drab for /, handling events in DrabTestApp.PageCommander
    You may debug Drab functions in IEx by copy/paste the following:
import Drab.Core; import Drab.Query; import Drab.Modal; import Drab.Waiter
socket = GenServer.call(pid("HERE BE PID"), :get_socket)
</pre>


    Examples:
<pre>
socket |> select(:htmls, from: "h3")
socket |> execjs("alert('hello from IEx!')")
socket |> alert("Title", "Sure?", buttons: [ok: "Azali≈º", cancel: "Poniechaj"])
</pre>

